# ===================================================================
# Limitless monorepo .gitignore
# ===================================================================
# Aggressive about NEVER committing:
#   - private keys (signing key for licenses; would compromise all licenses if leaked)
#   - SQLite databases (contain customer emails and license records)
#   - logs (large, contain PII)
#   - build output (regenerable, just bloats the repo)
#
# Aggressive about NEVER excluding:
#   - source code
#   - csproj / sln files
#   - configuration TEMPLATES (appsettings.json — but NOT appsettings.Production.json)
# ===================================================================

# --- SECRETS — MUST NEVER COMMIT ---
*.key
*.pem
*.pfx
keygen-private.key
keygen-private.txt
appsettings.Production.json
appsettings.Local.json
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- DATABASES ---
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
licenses.db*
ltc.db*

# --- LOGS ---
logs/
*.log
*.log.*

# --- .NET BUILD OUTPUT ---
bin/
obj/
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
[Dd]ebug/
[Rr]elease/
x64/
x86/
*.user
*.suo
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

# --- VISUAL STUDIO / RIDER ---
.vs/
.idea/
*.swp
*~

# --- TEST RESULTS ---
[Tt]est[Rr]esult*/
[Bb]uild[Ll]og.*
*.coverage
*.coveragexml

# --- OS FILES ---
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store
desktop.ini

# --- INSTALLER OUTPUT (these go on GitHub Releases, not in repo) ---
installer/Output/
obfuscation/Output/

# --- TEMP / SCRATCH ---
tmp/
temp/
scratch/
*.tmp
